; System suites for `fennec test system` (needs the built `fennec`). Each spawns the real
; `fennec dev`, drives its process/port/livereload lifecycle via Fennec_hunt.System, and asserts
; the observable side effects — replacing the old e2e/*.sh scripts with typed, deterministic tests.
;
; On a custom alias (@system), NOT @runtest: these launch `fennec dev`, which runs
; `dune build --watch`, so they must never run nested under dune. The CLI builds them one-shot,
; then runs the artifacts directly (the same lock-safe orchestration as the http/browser cuts).
(executables
 (names process_test domains_test livereload_test errors_test heal_test)
 (modules process_test domains_test livereload_test errors_test heal_test)
 (libraries fennec-hunt fennec-hunt.unit))

(rule
 (alias system)
 (deps
  process_test.exe
  domains_test.exe
  livereload_test.exe
  errors_test.exe
  heal_test.exe)
 (action (progn)))
